article.headline: San Francisco 82, CS Bakersfield 73
article.story: SAN FRANCISCO -- Dior Lowhorn had 27 points and nine rebounds, Kwame Vaughn added 22 points and San Francisco beat Cal State Bakersfield 82-73 to end a three-game losing streak Wednesday night. Lowhorn, the Dons' leading scorer, went 17 of 21 at the free throw line as San Francisco (4-9) won the first-ever meeting between the two schools. Donald Bragg had 14 points, seven rebounds and five assists for Bakersfield (1-9), which played the final 14:30 without leading scorer Trent Blakely. Blakely was ejected from the game after being called for a flagrant foul when he slammed Dons' freshman guard Mike Williams to the floor early in the second half, opening a cut over Williams' eye. The Dons trailed most of the first half but opened the second half with a 27-7 run to take control.
